  <h2>Miraloma Park</h2>

  <p>
    Our home is located in San Francisco's Miraloma Park neighborhood.  If you've never heard of it before, you're in good company -- most San Franciscans probably haven't either.  Some better-known neighborhoods that we border are Diamond Heights to the North and Glen Park to the East.  We are also close to West Portal.
  </p>

  <p>
    Most of Miraloma Park lies in San Francisco's fog belt, San Francisco being roughly divisible into three climate zones -- sun belt, fog belt, and the transition zone between the two (though the differences between the zones are most noticeable during our "wintry" summers).  What the neighborhood lacks in climate though it makes up for in views -- our hilly terrain gives us some of the best in The City.  And since we're sandwiched in between Mount Davidson Park and Glen Canyon Park, nature abounds. 
  </p>

  <p>
    There is very little information on the web about our neighborhood, but you can try the following link if you're interested in learning more:  <a href="http://www.sanfranciscodays.com/miraloma-park/">[CLICK HERE]</a>
  </p>

